<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08165a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08165a">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08165a"> 165(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> matin, chagrin / midi, souci / soir, espoir</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Popular Superstitions</b> How many a spider have I myself saved from an untimely end, and always paused meanwhile to remember the hour of the day, recalling the old French lines: &ldquo;Matin, chagrin; midi, souci; soir, espoir!&rdquo; / &ldquo;Morning, sorrow; midday, worry; evening, hope!&rdquo; Leonora MacNally <small> <a name="II9feb24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#II9feb24"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (9 February 1924) 5/3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
